<br>
I do agree with you about the &quot;games remaining the same&quot; thing (though the analogy to it being like life is a little off). Its true no matter what game you play....a certain manatony develops. I just finished Return to Castle Wolfenstein (which is a hoot!) and thier is no doubt the game play was the same from beginning to end but the keyword here is &quot;finished&quot;. Its a done deal. Now I move on to something else maybe. EQ just isnt like that. You could, literally, play FOREVER. I figure I could have maybe handled a few more levels of RtCW but in all honestly, it was starting to get a little boring. Much like EQ has. How many expansions can you handle?<br>
<br>
This has strayed from the threads original subject so i wont go any further with it. All i'm saying is EQ is going to suffer unless more than just expansions are added (or until EQ2 comes out). Yeah, all games are inherantly (sp?) the same but exactly how many of them could you play for years and years without any major modification? It may not happen today, or tomorrow, or even a year or two from now but someday....you WILL get bored.<br>
<br>
The only end to EQ will be the day it shuts down business. That is way to long for me to play, heheh.<br>
<br>
Anyway, sorry to stray from the subject. We now return you to your regularly scheduled thread.<br>
